let me start you out with the background of my microwave.  its at least 15 years old, and HUGE.  it takes double the time of a regular microwave to cook food all the way through.  so i was in the process of making a bowl of delicious sphagetti o's, and i took it out of the microwave.  the problem is the bowl is extreemly hot.  so i use a hot pad and i picked it up, and for some reason there was a hole in the pot holder.  so i burnt my hand really bad, and that made me tip over the searing hot bowl of sphagetti o's. some of this lava got on my nipple... it got everywhere else in the kitchen.

it burns like fire... and im more sad because i spilt half of my LAST can of sphagetti o's.

as much as id love to just add to the monstrosity below instead of moving on and making new journals, i wont.

not so often do i hate somthing, ok, well one thing that i hate is the movies.  everything about them sucks.  

starting with the price of movies, they keep on rising and rising.  its partially because we pay the actors 90843asdf984 million for a single role, and partially because i have no idea why but it should be stopped.

second, i HATE when young families bring their young children to any movie pg-13 and up.  its not daycare or a babysitter, its unfair to everyone trying to enjoy the already high priced movie.  i was sitting in spiderman 2 yesterday, and next to us was this 1 or two year old baby, who half the time cried and talked, and the other half walked around.  thats just rude to everyone else, and those people should be kicked out, or not allowed in for that matter.

third, pop corn.  of all the possible things they could have sold in a movie theatre, they had to sell a big tub of noisy, cracking (hence the name POP) corn.  when every person in the theatre is rustling through their bag to get the last few kernels, it takes away from the movie, which i paid nearly 10 dollars to see.  


ill add more if i remember anything of importance.

True words from a smart man. 

Which brings me to my point... im not saying hes not a really great film maker or not inteligent, but ive heard people (not picking on you brian) that say that his movies are great sources of information.  I cant really agree there because michael moore is an extreemly biased and one sided liberal.  His movies represent only one side of any issue, and to the uninformed masses, it can be viewed as fact, which would be wrong.  They should be viewed as entertainment and only entertainment, nothing more.  For it to be called a documentary is wrong and missleading.  

I have yet to see farienheit 9/11, but have seen bowling for columbine many times and will not pass judgement on 9/11 before i see it.  

Sidenote, i am also not a republican, i am a democrat, even if it may not seem that way.  I am a moderate middle of the road democrat, just for everyones knowledge.  Please feel free to comment or send death threats.

well its been a long time since i have updated... figured id give it a shot. i set up a myspace, been busy with that, ive nearly neglected my lj, but your used to it already. graduation has come and gone, and im sorta depressed about the whole thing. sure, yay, whole new live next year at santa cruz, but im really gonna miss the people in burbank. it feels like now more than ever im just recently getting to know alot of people better. on a lighter note, i bought a few cds this week (for those of you who know me, thats an amazing feat) i got the best of reggie n the full effect, and another year on the streets vol. 3 (vagrant yearly cd), and some random bob marley (definatly will be coming in handy next year at santa cruz). went up to orientation at santa cruz, registered in my classes, im official, cant believe it. dorms look awsome, brand new, co-ed floors and bathrooms, im not sure if thats a good thing or bad thing, but i had no choice. it will definatly be cleaner than an all guys bathroom. thats it, its kinda late, lots to do tomorow.

it finally hit me that schools over, im done with burbank, ill most likley never see most of the aquantances and some friends ive made over the past 4 years. its wierd how you meet so many more people towards the end, make so many more friends in the last year, and then you have to say goodbye. its more sad and unfair than anything. oh well, ill meet a whole new group of people up in santa cruz, and i still have the summer to say goodbye. all the freshmen ive just began to corrupt are growing up and are gonna be without me next year, eric coming back to burbank just when i leave... haha, that sucks. i still really really need to put my picture up on here.
